## 🔴 Lesson: ConversationHandler Fallbacks = CRITICAL (2026-05-30, 18:40 UTC)

**Bug:** Customer Bot booking flow text was going to Gemini AI because ConversationHandler had no fallbacks entry. Unmatched text exited the booking Conversation and was caught by the main text handler → Gemini AI.

**Fix:** Add `fallbacks=[MessageHandler(filters.TEXT & ~filters.COMMAND, bk_catch_all)]` to every ConversationHandler. `bk_catch_all` re-prompts user to use menu options rather than exiting to AI.

**Related:** `_bk_intercept_menu()` must be called in EVERY text-accepting state. 19 calls across 7 states now.

**Lesson:** ANY ConversationHandler with text-accepting states MUST have:
1. A `fallbacks` entry (catch-all so unmatched text stays in conversation)
2. Menu button interception in every state
3. Expanded skip keyword set (not just exact button labels)

